<br>
Prime example for us was several months ago when we took our first shots at Itraer Vius.  I laid down a strategy, and no one seemed to take hold, even the second time through.  After the second wipe, it was almost like I could just feel it coming over guild chat that they were expecting me to blow up.  I believe I started it out like, &quot;Ok guys I need to say a few things here..&quot;  One of the members piped in with, &quot;Brace yourselves..&quot;<br>
<br>
Simple dumb mistakes over and over again are agonizing when people just aren't paying attention, however it's the events where I notice that people are really trying to get a grasp on things are where I really need to get ahold of myself, and just keep pushing them on.<br>
<br>
Every guild has those days.  I hate them, but I think as a guild grows you look at those days and you realize how good they actually were for the guild, and how much you learned from them. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=466150">Marshall Lydell</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
